feat(cae-viz): peak/min field markers in the 3D viewer (#252)

Answers "where is the peak stress?" — marks the maximum (red) and minimum (blue)
node of the active result field in 3D, built on the field descriptor from #246/#251.

- fieldExtrema.ts (pure): findFieldExtrema(values, coords) locates the peak/min
  node + coordinate; skips non-finite values, tolerates length mismatch.
- fieldMarkers.ts: buildFieldMarkerGroup() places marker spheres at the extrema in
  display coordinates (modelToDisplayVec), sized to the model span, drawn over the
  model. Only real solver fields (source frd + per-node values) get markers — a
  synthetic descriptor yields none (honest).
- useFieldMarkerOverlay hook mirrors the proven assembly-check overlay pattern;
  useThreeScene gains a dedicated marker group.
- ModelViewer: a "Show peak/min" toggle (shown only when a real field is active),
  positioned bottom-left to avoid the picker/legend/assembly controls.

The peak/min VALUES already read off the legend (#246); these markers add the 3D
LOCATION. Interactive click-to-probe is a follow-up (noted on #252).

tsc clean; 185 vitest (incl. new fieldExtrema tests) green; production build OK.

